### Issue

- **What did you do?**
Train and evaluate LightGbmRanker using ML.Net C# API.
Training and test data are clustered/grouped with respect to GroupId column.

- **What happened?**
**Experiment 1:** Rows in Training data are sorted with respect to RankLabel, in this case rows corresponding to a GroupId have RankLabel 13, 12, 11, ........1, 1, 1, ..etc (Max rank is 13 for our use case)
**Experiment 2:** Rows in Training data are not sorted with respect to RankLabel, in this case rows corresponding to a GroupId have RankLabel in arbitrary order 
**TestData:** Even though test data has a RankLabel (for evaluation/ metric computation purpose), the rows corresponding to a GroupId are not sorted in any order.
- **Results:**
In case of experiment 1, NDCG score on TestData is quite high (around 0.95)
In case of experiment 2, NDCG score on TestData is quite low (around 0.25)

- **What did you expect?**
Same NDCG Score from both experiments.

